# Auto-commit and push

After making any code changes in this repository, run these three commands in order:

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "<concise summary of the changes we made>"
git push
```

- Use one `main` branch only — always push to the remote.
- Stage everything with `git add .`; the user manages exclusions via `.gitignore`.
- Do this automatically at the end of each task — the user does not need to ask separately.
- If push fails (e.g. network), report the failure and leave the commit local.
